The atomic bombs saved lots of American lives no doubt.<br>
You can argue whether it saved Japanese lives or not and that is your opinion I personally think it saved a culture.<br>
<br>
On to Star Wars of Reagan.  Star Wars was a vision.  He wanted it but the most useful purpose of it was telling the Russians that we had it. <br>
<br>
Although I tend to disagree with the idea of an Anti Ballistic Force for the simple reason it makes people forget about Eisenhower's policy of MAD mentioned above.  Mutually Assured Destruction has stopped us from going to war and destroying the Earth.  If you want a good example its when the Russians had a sane president and we had good ole wonder boy JFK.  JFK was ready to hit the button over the Cuban missile crisis when the Russians backed down.  Thank god that they did.  And I really see their point in wanting missiles here.  The common text book does not tell you this but we had nuclear weapons in Turkey whenever they wanted to put them in Cuba.  They just wanted to be on even ground.  The result of the Cuban Missile Crisis is that we withdrew our nuclear weapons from Turkey and they withdrew their support from Cuba. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9>OT/OOC Forum</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.2<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  